@node "ftpmail" "FTP-mail howto"

 @{b}How to make ftp by e-mail?@{ub}


 It's easy! Just send a e-mail to some ftp-mail server, containing ftp
commands in the body of message, just like a script.


 @{b}@{u}Some servers:@{ub}@{uu}
 @{i}(list i got from a friend, not all servers tested yet)@{ui}


   ftpmail@garbo.uwasa.fi         @{i}(Finland)@{ui}
   bitftp@vm.gmd.de               @{i}(Germany)@{ui}
   ftpmail@inf.tu-dresden.de      @{i}(Germany)@{ui}
   ftpmail@ftp.rz.uni-dresden.de  @{i}(Germany)@{ui}
   ftpmail@ieunet.ie              @{i}(Ireland)@{ui}
   bitftp@plearn.edu.pl           @{i}(Poland)@{ui}
   ftpmail@ftp.sunet.se           @{i}(Sweden)@{ui}
   ftpmail@ftp.luth.se            @{i}(Sweden)@{ui}
   bitftp@pucc.princeton.edu      @{i}(United States)@{ui}
   ftpmail@census.gov             @{i}(United States)@{ui}
   ftp-request@netcom.com         @{i}(United States)@{ui}
   ftpmail@ftpmail.ramona.vix.com @{i}(United States)@{ui}
   ftpmail@src.doc.ic.ac.uk       @{i}(United Kingdom)@{ui}
   ftpmail@conicit.ve             @{i}(Venezuela)@{ui}



@{b}@{u}Commands:@{ub}@{uu}

   @{b}open <site>@{ub} - connect to the indicated ftp server

   @{b}dir@{ub}         - show directory (sent to you by a message you'll receive)

   @{b}ls@{ub}          - show directory (simpler form)

   @{b}quit@{ub}        - end connection

   @{b}chdir@{ub} (use "cd" if "chdir" doesn't work) - change to directory

   @{b}get <name of file>@{ub} - the indicated file will be send to you.
        if it is a binary one (not plain text) you'll have to put before:

   @{b}binary@{ub} - says that the following "get" commands will send
            binary files.



@{b}@{u}Examples (body of message):@{ub}@{uu}



 1. Shows directory in /pub dir from ftp.uol.com.br

@{fg highlight} open ftp.uol.com.br
 chdir pub
 dir
 quit@{fg text}


 2. Get /pub/fruit/banana.zip file from ftp.abcdef.com

@{fg highlight} open ftp.abcdef.com
 chdir pub
 chdir fruit
 binary
 get banana.zip
 quit@{fg text}
@endnode

